    <h1>Mass test&#xAD;ing as cases emerge in Chengdu</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201210/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-10"><time>2020-12-10</time></a>
        - <span>WORLD</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>CHENGDU • The Chi­nese au­thor­i­ties have tested more than a quar­ter of a mil­lion peo­ple for the coro­n­avirus in the south-western city of Chengdu af­ter more cases of the virus were de­tected there on Tues­day.</p>
    <p>The new flare-up started with an el­derly cou­ple who tested pos­i­tive on Mon­day.</p>
    <p>The gov­ern­ment has or­dered schools in some dis­tricts to close and en­ter­tain­ment venues to limit their crowd ca­pac­ity.</p>
    <p>Mean­while, Sichuan province, where Chengdu is lo­cated, plans to vac­ci­nate its high-risk pop­u­la­tion by the year end, while the rest of the pop­u­la­tion is ex­pected to get vac­ci­nated next year.</p>


